2 organizations with a need to know;
3 (b) Its release is authorized in writing by the impaired individual;
4 (c) The committee is required to make a report to the board; or
5 (d) The information is subject to court order.
6 (8) Notwithstanding subsections (5) and (6) of this section, the board may publicly
7 disclose the basis of a disciplinary action provided that the board does not
8 disclose information furnished to or produced by the Well-being Committee.
9 Section 16. KRS 313.550 is amended to read as follows:
10 (1) A dental laboratory operating or doing business in Kentucky shall employ at least
11 one (1) of the following:
12 (a) A certified dental technician who shall supervise all work performed in
13 accordance with a written laboratory procedure work order issued by a dentist
14 licensed pursuant to this chapter; or
15 (b) A dentist licensed under[pursuant] to this chapter.
16 (2) A[No] dentist shall not use the services of any dental laboratory to construct, alter,
17 repair, or duplicate any denture, plate, bridge, splint, orthodontic, or prosthetic
18 appliance, without first furnishing the commercial dental laboratory a written
19 procedure work order. Both the commercial dental laboratory and the dentist
20 producing the work order shall keep a copy on file for two (2) years, and all
21 laboratory procedure work orders required by this subsection shall be open to
22 inspection by the board.
23 (3) A dental laboratory that employs or contracts with a dentist licensed
24 under[according to] this chapter may construct, alter, repair, or duplicate any
25 denture, plate, bridge, splint, orthodontic, or prosthetic appliance without a work
26 order from a referring dentist if the patient is seen, [or ]evaluated, or has his or
27 her[whose] care[ is] supervised by the referring dentist.
