HB077620.100 - 2110 - XXXX 4/1/2026 8:59 PM Engrossed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 776/EN
1 SECTION 17. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 313 IS CREATED TO
2 READ AS FOLLOWS:
3 KRS Chapter 313 may be cited as the Kentucky Dental Practice Act.
4 Section 18. KRS 304.17C-085 is amended to read as follows:
5 (1) As used in this section:
6 (a) "Contractual discount" means a percentage reduction from a provider's usual
7 and customary rate for covered services [and material ]required under a
8 participating provider agreement; and
9 (b) "Covered services":
10 1. Means services and materials for which:
11 a.[1.] Reimbursement from a plan is provided by the enrollee's plan
12 contract; or
13 b.[2.] Reimbursement would be available but for the application of the
14 enrollee's contractual limitations of deductibles, copayments,
15 coinsurance, or frequency limitations; and
16 2. Does not include services and materials for which reimbursement
17 would be available but for the application of the enrollee's contractual
18 limitation of an annual maximum benefit.
19 (2) A participating provider agreement shall not require a participating provider to
20 provide services to an enrollee at a fee set by or subject to the approval of the
21 limited health service benefit plan unless the services are covered services under the
22 participating provider agreement.
23 (3) A provider shall not charge more for services and materials that are noncovered
24 services under a limited health service benefit plan than the provider's rate for the
25 services and materials.
26 (4) The amount of a contractual discount shall not result in a fee that is less than the
27 limited health service benefit plan would pay for covered services but for the
Page 35 of 36
HB077620.100 - 2110 - XXXX 4/1/2026 8:59 PM Engrossed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 776/EN
1 application an enrollee's contractual limitations of deductibles, copayments,
2 coinsurance, or frequency limitations.
3 (5) Reimbursement paid by the limited health service benefit plan for covered services:
4 (a) Shall be reasonable; and
5 (b) Shall not provide nominal reimbursement in order to claim that services and
6 materials are covered services.
7 (6) The provisions of this section shall not be waived by contract. Any contractual
8 arrangement in conflict with this section or that purports to waive any
9 requirement of this section shall be void.
10 Section 19. Section 18 of this Act applies to contracts issued or renewed on or
11 after the effective date of Section 18 of this Act.
12 Section 20. Whereas it is critical to ensure that the practice of dentistry is
13 professional, safe, and protected for the well-being of the citizens of the Commonwealth,
14 an emergency is declared to exist, and Sections 1 to 17 of this Act take effect upon its
15 passage and approval by the Governor or upon its otherwise becoming a law.
